## Version Scheme

We follow [Semantic Versioning 2.0.0](https://semver.org/):

```
MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH[-PRERELEASE]

MAJOR: Breaking changes
MINOR: New features (backward compatible)
PATCH: Bug fixes (backward compatible)
PRERELEASE: preview, alpha, beta, rc
```

### Examples
- `0.4.0` - Stable release
- `0.5.0-preview` - Preview release
- `1.0.0-rc.1` - Release candidate
- `2.0.0-alpha.1` - Alpha release

## Release Channels

### Stable
- **Core Library**: NuGet packages
- **Frequency**: As needed (typically monthly)
- **Stability**: Production ready
- **Support**: Full support

### Preview
- **VS Extension**: VSIX packages
- **Frequency**: Feature-based
- **Stability**: Feature complete, testing phase
- **Support**: Community support

### Nightly (Future)
- **All Components**: CI/CD builds
- **Frequency**: Daily
- **Stability**: Experimental
- **Support**: No support

## Deprecation Policy

### Minor Version Deprecation
- Features marked deprecated in current minor version
- Will be removed in next major version
- At least 6 months notice

### Major Version Support
- Current major version: Full support
- Previous major version: Security fixes only (1 year)
- Older versions: No support

### Current Support Matrix

| Version | Status | Support Until | Notes |
|---------|--------|---------------|-------|
| 0.5.x | Preview | TBD | VS Extension preview |
| 0.4.x | Current | Active | Full support |
| 0.3.x | Previous | 2025-04-26 | Security fixes only |
| 0.2.x | EOL | - | No support |

## How to Check Version

### Sqlx Core Library
```csharp
// In your code
var version = typeof(SqlTemplateAttribute).Assembly.GetName().Version;
Console.WriteLine($"Sqlx Version: {version}");
```

### Sqlx.Generator
```bash
# Check NuGet package version
dotnet list package | grep Sqlx.Generator
```

### VS Extension
```
Visual Studio > Extensions > Manage Extensions > Installed > Sqlx
```

